    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-09-13T04:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-09-13T04:00:00-05:00" n="37"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d37">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">330/9–1351: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Greece</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Peurifoy</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Athens</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-09-13T11:00:00+02:00"
                            >September 13, 1951—11 a.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1239. Re <gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 1213, Sept 10, we have
                    discussed matter with <gloss target="#t_FonOff1">FonOff</gloss> which is cabling
                    Kyrou to make strong attempt rally other <gloss target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss>
                    delegates to Greece’s support. <gloss target="#t_FonOff1">FonOff</gloss> is
                    aware that we wld be prepared to support Grk candidacy but cld hardly do so
                    usefully unless other backing developed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Peurifoy</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
